RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 82. Claiming Purse 18500. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR THREE YEAR OLDS. Claiming Price $15,000 (Races Wh ere Entered For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VICTOR'S DEAL stalked the early pace from the fence, moved between rivals down the backside to engage the leader, took command midway on the turn and drew off as much best. FORWHOMTHEBELLTOLL unhurried for the first half mile, commenced a rally into the final bend and steadily closed ground to garner the place. LOOKIN AT JUSTICE tracked the leaders from the rail saving ground and made a mild late bid up the fence down the lane. BRIGHT BRIAN took the lead from the gate, set a well rated pace and weakened when challenged on the far turn. UNBRIDLED VICTOR raced three wide down the backside in striking position and continued one-paced failing to mount a rally. OH SO SOCIAL prompted the pace from three wide through the final bend and weakened in the stretch. GO NUTS was never a factor.

OCELIA slow early to trail the field, rallied three wide at the head of the lane, angled inside down the lane and finished willingly. DEEP DISH pressed from two wide dueling on the lead, was bumped by CORSIDAT in the turn, continued to duel to the quarter pole and gave way down the stretch. TATTERED HEART chased the pace from the rail and failed to mount a bid. SHAPE OF YOU stalked the pace from three wide to the top of the stretch and flattened out.
